Q: what will happen?
    my %hash = map (2,4), %array;
    my %hash = map (2,5,7), %array;
    my @b = map (2,4,7), @array;
         
A: Finnally, I found this is a silly question!
    my %hash = map (2,4), %arrar  
    equals:
    my %hahs = map (2,4);    # the comma ',' means the map function ends
    %array;   
    
    
